The article discusses a meeting that took place between the President and representatives from various community groups to discuss comprehensive immigration reform. The President emphasized the need for a bipartisan process and highlighted the Senate proposal and Schumer-Graham framework as a basis for this reform. He stressed the importance of securing the borders and holding both undocumented workers and unscrupulous employers accountable. The President also mentioned that he will be delivering a speech on the topic soon. Additionally, he expressed his views on the recently passed law in Arizona and noted that the Department of Justice was reviewing it.